Thomas Davis wrote:
> 2) reiserfs kept changing their on disk format until recently.  We can't
> just reformat 500gb of data every few weeks.
That newly created filesystems have a different disk format doesn't require that
old file reiserfs file systems change their format when the version of reiserfs
changes.  There is no need for you to reformat when we change disk formats.
